obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3016)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3016&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Antiquities and Art`
  line `Treasures Act, 1972.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and for`
  line `different States and any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be`
  line `construed as a reference to the coming into force of that provision`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 5th April, 1976, vide notification No. G.S.R. 279(E), dated 5th April, 1976, (except the State of Sikkim), see Gazette of`
  line `India, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `1st June, 1979, vide notification No. G.S.R. 312(E), dated 15th May, 1979 in respect of the State of Sikkim, the`
  line `provisions of ss. 2, 3, 4, 19, 20, 22, 24, sub-section (1) of s. 25, sub-section (1) of s. 26 and ss. 27, 28, 29, 30 and 31, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3(i)`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3017)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3017&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "antiquity" includes--`
  line
  line `(1) (i) any coin, sculpture, painting, epigraph or other work of art or craftsmanship;`
  line
  line `(ii) any article, object or thing detached from a building or cave;`
  line
  line `(iii) any article, object or thing illustrative of science, art, crafts, literature, religion, customs,`
  line `morals or politics in bygone ages;`
  line
  line `(iv) any article, object or thing of historical interest;`
  line
  line `(v) any article, object or thing declared by the Central Government, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, to be an antiquity for the purposes of this Act, which has been in existence for`
  line `not less than one hundred years; and`
  line
  line `(II) any manuscript, record or other document which is of scientific, historical, literary or`
  line `aesthetic value and which has been in existence for not less than seventy-five years;`
  line
  line `(b) "art treasure" means any human work of art, not being an antiquity, declared by the Central`
  line `Government by notification in the Official Gazette, to be an art treasure for the purposes of this Act`
  line `having regard to its artistic or aesthetic value:`
  line
  line `Provided that no declaration under this clause shall be made in respect of any such work of art so`
  line `long as the author thereof is alive;`
  line
  line `(c) "export" means taking out of India to a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(d) "licensing officer" means an officer appointed as such under section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) "registering officer" means an officer appointed as such under section 15;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to any law which is not In force in any area shall, in relation to that area,`
  line `be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3018)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Regulation of export trade in antiquities and art treasures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3018&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the`
  line `commencement of this Act, it shall not be lawful for any person, other than the Central Government or`
  line `any authority or agency authorized by the Central Government in this behalf, to export any antiquity or`
  line `art treasure.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever the Central Government or any authority or agency referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `intends to export any antiquity or art treasure such export shall be made only under and in accordance`
  line `with the terms and conditions of a permit issued for the purpose by such authority as may be prescribed`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3019)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Application of Act 52 of 1962.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3019&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Customs Act, 1962, shall have effect in relation to all`
  line `antiquities and art treasures, the export of which by any person (other than the Central Government or any`
  line `authority or agency authorized by the Central Government) is prohibited under section 3 save in so far as`
  line `that Act is inconsistent with the provisions of this Act and except that (notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 125 of that Act) any confiscation authorized under that Act shall be made unless the`
  line `Central Government on an application made to it in this behalf, otherwise directs`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3020)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Antiquities to be sold only under a licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3020&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[As from the date of expiry of a period of six`
  line `months from the commencement of this Act] no person shall, himself or by any other person on his`
  line `behalf, carry on the business of selling or offering to sell any antiquity except under and in accordance`
  line `with the terms and conditions of a licence granted under section 8.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section and in sections 7, 8, 12, 13, 14, 17 and 18 antiquity does not include`
  line `ancient and historical records other than those declared by or under law made by Parliament, to be of`
  line `national importance.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 82 of 1976, s. 2, for "On and from the expiry of a period of two months of the commencement of this Act"`
  line `(w.e.f. 4-6-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3021)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Appointment of licensing officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3021&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notified order,--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint such persons, being gazetted officers of Government, as it thinks fit, to be licensing`
  line `officers for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) define the limits of the area within which a licensing officer shall exercise the powers`
  line `conferred on licensing officers by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3022)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Application for licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3022&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person desiring to carry on, himself or by any other person on`
  line `his behalf, the business of selling or offering to sell antiquities may make an application for the grant of a`
  line `licence to the licensing officer having jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form and shall contain such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3023)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Grant of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3023&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an application for the grant of a licence under section 7, the`
  line `licensing officer may, after holding such inquiry as he deems fit, grant a licence to the applicant having`
  line `regard to the following factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the experience of the applicant with respect to trade in antiquities;`
  line
  line `(b) the village, town or city where the applicant intends to carry on business;`
  line
  line `(c) the number of persons already engaged in the business of selling, or offering for sale of,`
  line `antiquities in the said village, town or city; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other factors as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no licence shall be granted to the applicant if he is convicted of an offence`
  line `punishable under the Antiquities (Export Control) Act, 1947 (31 of 1947) unless a period of ten years`
  line `has elapsed since the date of the conviction.`
  line
  line `(2) Every licence granted under this section shall be on payment of such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every licence granted under this section shall be for such period, subject to such conditions and in`
  line `such form and shall contain such particulars, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) No application for the grant of a licence made under section 7 shall be rejected unless the`
  line `applicant has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3024)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Renewal of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3024&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) A licence granted under section 8 may, on an application made by the`
  line `licensee, be renewed by the licensing officer for such period and on payment of such fees as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) No application made under this section shall be rejected unless the applicant has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3025)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Maintenance of records, photographs and registers by licensees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3025&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every holder of a`
  line `licence granted under section 8 or renewed under section 9 shall maintain such records, photographs and`
  line `registers, in such manner and containing such particulars, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every record, photograph and register maintained under sub-section (1) shall, at all reasonable`
  line `times, be open to inspection by the licensing officer or by any other gazetted officer of Government`
  line `authorised in writing by the licensing officer in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3026)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Revocation, suspension and amendment of licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3026&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the licensing officer is satisfied`
  line `either on a reference made to him in this behalf or otherwise that--`
  line
  line `(a) a licence granted under section 8 has been obtained by misrepresentation of an essential`
  line `fact, or`
  line
  line `(b) the holder of a licence has, without reasonable cause, failed to comply with the conditions`
  line `subject to which the licence has been granted or has contravened any of the provisions of this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder,`
  line
  line `then, without prejudice to any other penalty to which the holder of the licence may be liable under this`
  line `Act, the licensing officer may, after giving the holder of the licence an opportunity of showing cause,`
  line `revoke or suspend the licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, the licensing officer may also vary or amend`
  line `a licence granted under section 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3027)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Persons whose licences have been revoked may sell antiquities to other licensees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3027&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 5, any person whose licence has been revoked`
  line `under section 11 may, after making a declaration before the licensing officer, within such period, in such`
  line `form and in such manner, as may be prescribed, of all the antiquities in his ownership, control or`
  line `possession immediately before such revocation, sell such antiquities to any other person holding a valid`
  line `licence under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such antiquity shall be sold after the expiry of a period of six months from the date`
  line `of revocation of the licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3028)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of Central Government to carry on the business of selling antiquities to the exclusion of others.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3028&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is of opinion that with a view to conserving antiquities or in`
  line `the public interest it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `declare that with effect on and from such date as may be specified in the notification, the Central`
  line `Government or any authority or agency authorised by the Central Government in this behalf shall alone`
  line `be entitled to carry on the business of selling or offering for sale of antiquities.`
  line
  line `(2) On the issue of a notification under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) it shall not be lawful for any person, authority or agency, other than the Central Government`
  line `or any authority or agency authorized by the Central Government, to carry on the business of selling`
  line `or offering for sale any antiquity on and from the date specified therein;`
  line
  line `(b) the provisions of this Act, in so far as they relate to the licensing of persons carrying on the`
  line `business of selling or offering for sale of antiquities shall cease to have effect except as respects`
  line `things done or omitted to be done before such cesser of operation and section 6 of the General`
  line `Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) shall apply upon such cesser of operation as if those provisions had`
  line `been repealed by a Central Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that every licence granted under section 8 and in force on the date aforesaid shall,`
  line `notwithstanding that the period specified therein has not expired, cease to be in force.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person whose licence has ceased to be in force under the proviso to clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2) shall, within such period, in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, make a`
  line `declaration before the licensing officer of all the antiquities in his ownership, control or possession`
  line `immediately before the date specified in the notification issued under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3029)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Registration of antiquities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3029&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, from time to time, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify those antiquities which shall be registered under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In specifying the antiquities under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall have regard to`
  line `the following factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the necessity for conserving the objects of art;`
  line
  line `(ii) the need to preserve such objects within India for the better appreciation of the cultural`
  line `heritage of India;`
  line
  line `(iii) such other factors as will, or are likely to, contribute to the safeguarding of the cultural`
  line `heritage of India.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who owns, controls or is in possession of any antiquity specified in the notification`
  line `issued under sub-section (1) shall register such antiquity before the registering officer--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a person who owns, controls or possesses such antiquity on the date of issue of`
  line `such notification, within three months of such date; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other person, within fifteen days of the date on which he comes into`
  line `ownership, control or possession of such antiquity,`
  line
  line `and obtain a certificate in token of such registration`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (3030)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Appointment of registering officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3030&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notified order,--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint such persons, as it thinks fit, to be registering officers for the purposes of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) define the limits of the area within which a registering officer shall exercise the powers`
  line `conferred on registering officers by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (3031)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Application for registration and grant of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 82 of 1976, s. 3, for "shall be accompanied" (w.e.f. 4-6-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3031&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person`
  line `required to register any antiquity before the registering officer under section 14 shall make an application`
  line `to the registering officer for the grant of a certificate of registration.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) ^1shall, in the case of such antiquities or class of`
  line `antiquities as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify, be`
  line `accompanied] by such photographs of the antiquity which is to be registered and by such number of`
  line `copies, not exceeding six, as may be prescribed and shall be made in such form and shall contain such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the registering officer may, after holding such`
  line `inquiry as he deems fit, grant a certificate of registration containing such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) No application made under this section shall be rejected unless the applicant has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (3032)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Transfer of ownership, etc., of antiquities to be intimated to the registering officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3032&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person transfers the ownership, control or possession of any antiquity specified`
  line `in any notification issued under sub-section (1) of section 14 such person shall intimate, within such`
  line `period and in such form as may be prescribed, the fact of such transfer to the registering officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (3033)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Provisions of sections 14, 16 and 17 not to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `4. Ins. by Act 82 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 4-6-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3033&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in section 14 or`
  line `section 16 or section 17 shall apply to any antiquity kept--`
  line
  line `(i) in a museum; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in an office; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in an archive; or`
  line
  line `(iv) in an educational or cultural institution,`
  line
  line `owned, controlled or managed by the Government ^1[or by any local authority or by any such body as the`
  line `Central Government may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, approve for the purpose of this section by`
  line `general or special order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (3034)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of Central Government to compulsorily acquire antiquities and art treasures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3034&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `the Central Government is of opinion that it is desirable to preserve any antiquity or art treasure in a`
  line `public place, that Government may make an order for the compulsory acquisition of such antiquity or art`
  line treasure.
  line
  line `(2) On the making of an order under sub-section (1) the Collector of the district in which such`
  line `antiquity or art treasure is kept shall give notice to the owner thereof intimating him of the decision of the`
  line `Central Government to acquire the same and it shall be lawful for the Collector to take possession of such`
  line `antiquity or art treasure, for which purpose the Collector may use such force as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the owner of any antiquity or art treasure the possession of which has been taken over by`
  line `the Collector under sub-section (2) objects to the taking over of such possession, he may, within a period`
  line `of thirty days from the date on which such possession was taken over, make a representation to the`
  line `Central Government putting forth his objections:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may entertain the representation after the expiry of the said`
  line `period of thirty days, if it is satisfied that the owner of such antiquity or art treasure was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from making the representation in time.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of any representation under sub-section (3), the Central Government, after making such`
  line `inquiry as it deems fit and after giving to the objector an opportunity of being heard in the matter, shall,`
  line `within a period of ninety days from the date of receipt of the representation, either rescind or confirm the`
  line `order made by it under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) Where any order made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) is rescinded under`
  line `sub-section (4) the antiquity or art treasure shall be returned to the owner thereof without delay and at the`
  line `expense of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the order made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) is confirmed under`
  line `sub-section (4) the antiquity or art treasure shall vest in the Central Government with effect from the date`
  line `on which the possession thereof has been taken over by the Collector under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(7) The power of compulsory acquisition conferred by this section shall not extend to any object,`
  line `being an antiquity or art treasure, used for bona fide religious observances.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "public place" means any place which is open to the use of the public,`
  line `whether on payment of fees or not, or whether it is actually used by the public or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (3035)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Payment of compensation for antiquities and art treasures compulsorily acquired under section 19.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3035&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any antiquity or art treasure is compulsorily acquired under section 19, there shall`
  line `be paid compensation, the amount of which shall be determined in the manner and in accordance with the`
  line `principles hereinafter set out, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the amount of compensation can be fixed by agreement, it shall be paid in accordance`
  line `with such agreement;`
  line
  line `(b) where no such agreement can be reached, the Central Government shall appoint as arbitrator a`
  line `person who is, or has been, or is qualified for appointment as, a Judge of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(c) the Central Government may, in any particular case, nominate a person having expert`
  line `knowledge as to the nature of the antiquity or art treasure compulsorily acquired to assist the`
  line `arbitrator and where such nomination is made, the person to be compensated may also nominate an`
  line `assessor for the same purpose;`
  line
  line `(d) at the commencement of the proceedings before the arbitrator, the Central Government and`
  line `the person to be compensated shall state what, in their respective opinion, is a fair amount of`
  line compensation;
  line
  line `(e) the arbitrator shall, after hearing the dispute, make an award determining the amount of`
  line `compensation which appears to him to be just and specifying the person or persons to whom such`
  line `compensation shall be paid and in making the award he shall have regard to the circumstances of each`
  line `case and the provisions of sub-section (2);`
  line
  line `(f) where there is any dispute as to the person or persons who are entitled to the compensation, the`
  line `arbitrator shall decide such dispute and if the arbitrator finds that more persons than one are entitled`
  line `to compensation, he shall apportion the amount thereof amongst such persons;`
  line
  line `(g) nothing in the Arbitration Act, 1940 (10 of 1940) shall apply to arbitration under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) While determining the compensation under sub-section (1), the arbitrator shall have regard to the`
  line `following factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the date or the period to which the antiquity or art treasure belongs;`
  line
  line `(ii) the artistic, aesthetic, historical, architectural, archaeological or anthropological importance of`
  line `the antiquity or art treasure;`
  line
  line `(iii) the rarity of the antiquity or art treasure;`
  line
  line `(iv) such other matters as are relevant to the dispute.`
  line
  line `(3) The arbitrator appointed under sub-section (1), while holding arbitration proceedings under this`
  line `section, shall have all the powers of a Civil Court, while trying a suit, under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (3036)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Appeals against decisions of licensing officers and registering officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3036&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person`
  line `aggrieved by a decision of a licensing officer under section 8 or section 9 or section 11 or by a decision of`
  line `a registering officer under section 16 may, within thirty days from the date on which the decision is`
  line `communicated to him, prefer an appeal to such authority as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in`
  line time.
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the appellate authority shall, after giving the`
  line `appellant an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders as it deems fit`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (3037)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Appeals against awards of arbitrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3037&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an award of the arbitrator`
  line `made under section 20 may, within thirty days from the date on which the award is communicated to him,`
  line `prefer an appeal to the High Court within whose jurisdiction he resides:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty days`
  line `if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by a sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (3038)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Powers of entry, search, seizure, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3038&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, being an officer of Government,`
  line `authorized in this behalf by the Central Government, may, with a view to securing compliance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act or to satisfying himself that the provisions of this Act have been complied with`
  line
  line `(i) enter and search any place;`
  line
  line `(ii) seize any antiquity or art treasure in respect of which he suspects that any provision of this`
  line `Act has been, is being, or is about to be, contravened and thereafter take all measures necessary for`
  line `securing the production of the antiquity or art treasure so seized in a court and for its safe custody,`
  line `pending such production.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 102 and 103 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)`
  line `relating to search and seizure shall, so far as may be, apply to searches and seizures under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (3039)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to determine whether or not an article, etc., is antiquity or art treasure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3039&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `If any`
  line `question arises whether any article, object or thing or manuscript, record or other document is or is not an`
  line `antiquity or is or is not an art treasure for the purposes of this Act, it shall be referred to the Director`
  line `General, Archaeological Survey of India, or to an officer not below the rank of a Director in the`
  line `Archaeological Survey of India authorized by the Director General, Archaeological Survey of India and`
  line `the decision of the Director General, Archaeological Survey of India or such officer, as the case may be,`
  line `on such question shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (3040)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3040&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person, himself or by any other person on his behalf, exports or attempts to`
  line `export any antiquity or art treasure in contravention of section 3, he shall, without prejudice to any`
  line `confiscation or penalty to which he may be liable under the provisions of the Customs`
  line `Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) as applied by section 4, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than six months but which may extend to three years and with fine.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person contravenes the provisions of section 5 or section 12 or sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 13 or section 14 or section 17, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to six months or with fine or with both and the antiquity in respect of which the`
  line `offence has been committed shall be liable to confiscation.`
  line
  line `(3) if any person prevents any licensing officer from inspecting any record, photograph or register`
  line `maintained under section 10 or prevents any officer authorized by the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 23 from entering into or searching any place under that sub-section, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (3041)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3041&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No prosecution for an offence under sub-section (1) of section 25`
  line `shall be instituted except by or with the sanction of such officer of Government as may be prescribed in`
  line `this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 25 except upon complaint in writing made by an officer generally or specially authorized in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) No court inferior to that of a Presidency Magistrate or a Magistrate of the First Class shall try any`
  line `offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (3042)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Magistrate’s power to impose enhanced penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3042&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 32 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), it shall be lawful for any Presidency`
  line `Magistrate or any Magistrate of the First Class to pass any sentence under this Act in excess of his power`
  line `under section 32 of the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (3043)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3043&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, or was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment under this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of any director,`
  line `manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall`
  line `also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (3044)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3044&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government or any officer of the Government for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `is intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (3045)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3045&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of the Ancient Monuments Preservation Act, 1904 (7 of 1904) or the`
  line `Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains Act, 1958 (24 of 1958), or any other law for`
  line `the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (3046)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3046&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for`
  line
  line `(a) the authority for issue of permit under sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the form in which an application for the grant of a licence may be made under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 7 and the particulars which such application shall contain;`
  line
  line `(c) the factors to which regard may be had while granting a licence under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) the fees on payment of which, the period for which, the conditions subject to which and the`
  line `form in which a licence may be granted under sub-section (1) of section 8 and the particulars which`
  line `such licence shall contain;`
  line
  line `(e) the fees on payment of which and the period for which a licence may be renewed under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(f) the records, photographs and registers which are to be maintained under section 10 and the`
  line `manner in which such records, photographs and registers shall be maintained and the particulars`
  line `which such records, photographs and registers shall contain;`
  line
  line `(g) the nature of the photographs of the antiquity and the number of copies thereof which shall`
  line `accompany an application for the grant of a certificate of registration to be made under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 16 and the form in which such application may be made and the particulars`
  line `which such application shall contain;`
  line
  line `(h) the particulars which a certificate of registration granted under sub-section (3) of section 16`
  line `shall contain;`
  line
  line `(i) the authority to which an appeal may be preferred under sub-section (1) of section 21; and`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which has to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (3047)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3047&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Antiquities (Export Control) Act, 1947 (3 of 1947) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts it is hereby declared that every licence issued under section 3 of the Act`
  line `repealed under sub-section (1) and in force at the commencement of this Act shall, notwithstanding that`
  line `the period specified therein has not expired, cease to be in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (3048)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Amendment of Act 24 of 1958.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344&sectionId=3048&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00009_197252_1517807324344
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `In the Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and`
  line `Remains Act, 1958,--`
  line
  line `(i) in section 1, for sub-section (2), the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) It extends to the whole of India.";`
  line
  line `(ii) after section 2, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"2A. Construction of references to any law not in force in the State of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir.-- Any reference in this Act to any law which is not in force in the State of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir* shall, in relation to that State, be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if`
  line `any, in force in that State.";`
  line
  line `(iii) in section 23,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-sections (2) and (4), for the words "compulsory purchase", the words "compulsory`
  line `acquisition" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3), for the words "compulsory purchase of any such antiquities at their`
  line `market value", the words "compulsory acquisition of any such antiquities" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(iv) in section 26,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the words compulsory purchase of such antiquity at its market`
  line `value", the words "compulsory acquisition of such antiquity" and for the words "to be`
  line `purchased", the words "to be acquired" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-sections (2) and (3), for the words "compulsory purchase", the words "compulsory`
  line `acquisition" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(v) in section 28, for sub-section (2), the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) For every antiquity in respect of which an order for compulsory acquisition has been`
  line `made under sub-section (3) of section 23 or under sub-section (1) of section 26, there shall be`
  line `paid compensation and the provisions of sections 20 and 22 of the Antiquities and Art Treasures`
  line `Act, 1972 shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to the determination and payment of such`
  line `compensation as they apply in relation to the determination and payment of compensation for any`
  line `antiquity or art treasure compulsorily acquired under section 19 of that Act.".`
